# WhatsApp Alerting System Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the integration of a WhatsApp notification system to alert administrators when critical system health metrics (Database, Redis, OpenAI) fail.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This implementation requires a WhatsApp-capable API provider. I will initially implement a provider-agnostic notification service, but we will need to configure credentials (e.g., Twilio ACCOUNT_SID/AUTH_TOKEN) to go live.

## Proposed Changes

### Notification Service

#### [NEW] [whatsapp.ts](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/lib/whatsapp.ts)
*   Create a utility to send WhatsApp messages.
*   Support for a primary and fallback provider if needed.
*   Integration with environment variables for credentials.

### Health Check Integration

#### [MODIFY] [route.ts](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/app/api/health/route.ts)
*   Update the health check route to trigger a WhatsApp alert if a service is detected as `unhealthy`.
*   Implement cooldown logic (e.g., don't send an alert every time the endpoint is polled if it stays down).

### SRE Monitoring

#### [NEW] [health-monitor.ts](file:///c:/Users/fmonf/Desktop/Software%20Enginnering%20LAPTOP/Agencia%20B2B/agencia-web-b2b/src/lib/sre/health-monitor.ts)
*   A background process (or a Cron task via GitHub Actions/VPS Cron) that periodically hits the health endpoint and triggers notifications.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
*   Unit tests for the WhatsApp service with mocked API responses.
*   Integration tests for the health check trigger logic.

### Manual Verification
*   Send a test WhatsApp message to the configured administrator number.
*   Temporarily simulate a database failure to verify the alert is triggered.
